cs671

Interface TestResult


  • public interface TestResult
    Test result. A TestResult object is created for each test that is run and contains information on the test, as decribed below. Instances of this class are immutable.
    Version:
    2.0, 01/26/14
    Author:
    Michel Charpentier

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • getInfo

        String getInfo()
        Test info. If the info argument of the TestMethod annotation of the corresponding test method is not empty, then this is full-method-name + ": " + info; otherwise, it is full-method-name.
        See Also:
        TestMethod.info()

      • getWeight

        double getWeight()
        Test weight. This is the weight associated with the TestMethod annotation of the corresponding test method.
        See Also:
        TestMethod.weight()

      • getDuration

        double getDuration()
        Test duration. This is the duration of the test, in seconds, till completion or up to the point of failure. It does not include time spent inside beforeMethod and afterMethod.
        See Also:
        Testable.beforeMethod(java.lang.reflect.Method), Testable.afterMethod(java.lang.reflect.Method)

      • success

        boolean success()
        Test status.
        Returns:
        true if the test was successful, false otherwise

      • error

        Throwable error()
        Test failure.
        Returns:
        the cause of test failure, or null if the test was successful
